The paper deals with information theory and communication systems, specifically the capacity region of a multiple access channel with feedback. Therefore, cs.IT (Information Theory) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves networked systems and communication protocols, which fall under cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). The use of directed information and ergodic theory suggests a focus on mathematical foundations, which could place the paper in cs.LG (Machine Learning) or cs.MM (Multimedia).
